TITLE: Migrants crossing illegally into California snap photos at border wall
SUMMARY: Video captured by Fox News shows hundreds of migrants crossing the southern border illegally early Tuesday, with a group of them stopping to take photos at a section of border wall.

TITLE: Left-leaning attorney speaks out against DEI after he’s targeted twice by anti-Israel agitators
SUMMARY: A Jewish lawyer at a Michigan law firm was targeted for a second time on Monday morning in what the law firm is calling an "antisemitic attack."

TITLE: Jeffrey Epstein accuser claims psychiatrist made her 'sex slave’ in new lawsuit
SUMMARY: Lawsuit alleges Henry Jarecki, a prominent psychiatrist, academic and businessman, made a model into his "sex slave" after Jeffrey Epstein sent her to him.

TITLE: Chicago couple brutally assaulted by teens while on date, pregnant wife loses baby after attack
SUMMARY: A Chicago husband and wife were assaulted Friday while on a date night in the city's Streeterville neighborhood by a group of teens who said, "we own the street," according to one victim.

TITLE: Yellowstone bison gores 83-year-old tourist, lifting her off the ground
SUMMARY: An 83-year-old woman from South Carolina was lifted about a foot off the ground while being gored by a bison inside Yellowstone National Park, officials say.

TITLE: Hot air balloon crashes into Indiana power lines, injuring 3
SUMMARY: Three people were injured with burns when a hot air balloon collided with power lines in northwest Indiana over the weekend, fire officials confirmed. The FAA is investigating the cause.

TITLE: Ex-US soldier accused of Florida double murder, ‘international crime spree’: feds
SUMMARY: Arizona resident and former U.S. soldier Craig Austin Lang allegedly robbed and killed a Florida couple in 2018, among other crimes, federal prosecutors said

TITLE: Ohio woman accused of stabbing 3-year-old boy to death in 'random' parking lot attack
SUMMARY: Julian Wood, 3, has died after allegedly being stabbed in a "random" attack outside of a Giant Eagle supermarket in North Olmsted, Ohio, police say.

TITLE: TikTok acts as 'virtual strip club,' allowing adults to pay for kids' content, Utah lawsuit alleges
SUMMARY: A Utah lawsuit is accusing TikTok of harming children through LIVE, arguing that the app's streaming feature acts as a 'virtual strip club' in which preying adults can pay for content.

TITLE: Rodeo star's son Levi Wright dies after Utah river accident: report
SUMMARY: Saddle bronc champion Spencer Wright's toddler, Levi, died less than two weeks after falling into a Utah river, family and friends said.

TITLE: New Orleans student graduates as valedictorian after living in homeless shelter
SUMMARY: Elijah Hogan graduated from Walter L. Cohen charter high school in New Orleans as one of two valedictorians after living in a homeless shelter for youth for more than a year.

TITLE: Three boys discover rare T.rex fossil in North Dakota
SUMMARY: Three young boys discovered a Tyrannosaurus rex fossil nearly two years ago, and this summer their find will be featured in a documentary while a museum continues work to fully uncover.

TITLE: Anti-Israel agitators occupy Israeli Consulate in San Francisco before police arrest 69
SUMMARY: The San Francisco Police Department responded to the Israeli Consulate Monday after nearly 100 anti-Israel demonstrators stormed and occupied the building before being removed.

TITLE: Families of hostages taken in Israel on Oct. 7 plead for peace at interfaith conference in NYC
SUMMARY: Family members of Hamas captives taken on Oct. 7 came together with religious leaders for an interfaith conference in New York City Monday amid the ongoing war in Gaza.

TITLE: DC carjacker crashes near US Attorney's office, elderly woman inside vehicle dies: police
SUMMARY: A female suspect stole a car from Washington Hospital and crashed it near the U.S. attorney's office, with an elderly passenger dying, D.C. police said.

TITLE: Opening statements to begin in Hunter Biden's criminal trial and more headlines
SUMMARY: Get all the stories you need-to-know from the most powerful name in news delivered first thing every morning to your inbox.

TITLE: Serial killer’s daughter confronts him behind bars over explosive diary entry that suggests she too was victim
SUMMARY: Kerri Rawson, the daughter of serial killer BTK, made a shocking discovery while helping cold case investigators look into her dad.

TITLE: Anti-Israel demonstrators set up unapproved encampment outside Los Angeles City Hall: police
SUMMARY: Anti-Israel protesters set up an encampment in front of Los Angeles City Hall to demand the city disclose and divest from any financial ties to Israel.

TITLE: Mexican kidnappers crossed US border to collect ransom, left hostage tied up in trench: docs
SUMMARY: Members of a Mexican family allegedly kidnapped a Los Angeles man in a violent abduction that was recorded and sent to family members with ransom demands

TITLE: JonBenet Ramsey’s father John claims Colorado police officer said they are ‘just waiting' for him to die
SUMMARY: John Ramsey, JonBenet Ramsey's father, continues to push for answers from the Boulder Police Department. He says an officer within the apartment said they are 'just waiting' for Ramsey to 'die.'

TITLE: Former Georgia police officer charged with teen girl's murder rejects plea deal
SUMMARY: A former Georgia police officer charged with the murder of a 16-year-old girl rejected the prosecution's plea deal before jury selection began Monday.

TITLE: Man who went viral for driving during virtual court hearing for suspended license reportedly vindicated
SUMMARY: A Michigan man has been vindicated after his driver's license suspension was actually rescinded but never updated in the court system, according to reports.

TITLE: Unlikely item saves Colorado man's life in shooting: ‘Likely the only reason’ he survived
SUMMARY: Police in Commerce City, Colorado, said a man's life was saved after a necklace he was wearing stopped a bullet shot at him during an argument.

TITLE: 450-pound bear reportedly killed in self-defense in Connecticut
SUMMARY: Police in Connecticut are investigating the fatal shooting of a 450-pound, adult male black bear whose killer claims the act was done in self-defense.

TITLE: Bodies of missing Minnesota fishermen pulled from Boundary Waters
SUMMARY: The bodies of missing fishermen Melvin Grams and Jesse Haugen, who went over a waterfall in Minnesota's Boundary Waters Canoe Area Wilderness, have been found.
